# 🧠 STEP 2 — Implement deck actions

## 📍 EDIT: `src/tabletop/state.cljs`

### Replace logic from existing functions with methods

---

### 🃏 Shuffle

```clojure
(defmethod perform-action [:deck :shuffle]
  [state id _]
  (update state :components
          (fn [cs]
            (mapv (fn [c]
                    (if (= (:id c) id)
                      (update c :cards shuffle)
                      c))
                  cs))))
```

---

### 🃏 Draw to hand

```clojure
(defmethod perform-action [:deck :draw-to-hand]
  [state id _]
  (let [[deck others] (reduce
                       (fn [[d rest] c]
                         (if (= (:id c) id)
                           [c rest]
                           [d (conj rest c)]))
                       [nil []]
                       (:components state))
        card (first (:cards deck))]
    (if card
      (-> state
          (assoc :components
                 (conj (vec others)
                       (update deck :cards subvec 1)))
          (update :hand conj card))
      state)))
```

---

### 🃏 Draw to table

```clojure
(defmethod perform-action [:deck :draw-to-table]
  [state id _ x y]
  (let [[deck others] (reduce
                       (fn [[d rest] c]
                         (if (= (:id c) id)
                           [c rest]
                           [d (conj rest c)]))
                       [nil []]
                       (:components state))
        card (first (:cards deck))]
    (if card
      (-> state
          (assoc :components
                 (conj (vec others)
                       (update deck :cards subvec 1)
                       (assoc card :x x :y y)))
          )
      state)))
```

---

### 🃏 Flip

```clojure
(defmethod perform-action [:deck :flip]
  [state id _]
  (update state :components
          (fn [cs]
            (mapv (fn [c]
                    (if (= (:id c) id)
                      (update c :cards reverse)
                      c))
                  cs))))
```

